%N A084815 Least integers that satisfy Sum_{n>=1} 1/a(n)^z = 0, where a(1)=1, a(n+1) > a(n) and z = i*Pi/4.
%C A084815 Sequence satisfies Sum_{n>=1} 1/a(n)^z = 0 by requiring that the modulus of the successive partial sums are monotonically decreasing in magnitude for the given z.
%C A084815 |Sum_{k=1..n} 1/a(k)^z| appears to converge geometrically to 0.970295166... Does this behavior continue? If this is true then the complex sum converges to a circular orbit rather than a single value. - _Martin Fuller_, May 24 2026
%o A084815 (PARI) my(z = I*Pi/4, S=0, w=1, a=0); for(n=1,100,b=a+1; while(abs(S+exp(-z*log(b)))>w,b++); S=S+exp(-z*log(b)); w=abs(S); a=b; print1(b,", "))
%o A084815 (PARI) \\ See Fuller link in A084813
